AJAX Cape Town have announce the signing of veteran defender Siboniso Gaxa.The former Mamelodi Sundowns and Kaizer Chiefs defender who has close to 300 Absa Premiership appearances have been training with Urban Warriors for the past few weeks, and the club have finnaly confirmed that they have signed him.Gaxa is in line to make his Urban Warriors debut this Sunday when Ajax visit Polokwane City.Quoted from the club website Gaxa said: "I’m delighted to have joined Ajax Cape Town and I am really grateful to head coach Muhsin [Ertugral] and the management for the opportunity to play football again“I am well aware of the situation the club finds itself in at the moment and I just want to help with my experience, I’ve played professionally for well over a decade and I believe I can contribute on and off the field in assisting this club move up the log standings.Gaxa continued: “What I have seen here [at Ikamva], the talent is amazing, the club structure is something that has really impressed me and I am grateful to be part of this unique institution.“I am really grateful to Mushin for showing faith in me and I can’t wait to start my journey here,” he concludedLike this story? Get the free Daily Kick App today and stay on top of your game with only the best from SunSport, Soccer Laduma, KickOff and many more!ALL YOUR SOCCER AND NEWS IN ONE PLACE THATHA ZONKE